  "text": "Edition-specific import path handling in Rust compiler (rust-lang/rust) is implemented across multiple locations:\n\n**Prelude Definition and Export (library/):**\n\nThe compiler defines edition-specific prelude modules in both std and core:\n- library/core/src/prelude/mod.rs (lines 12-95): Defines rust_2015, rust_2018, rust_2021, rust_2024, and rust_future prelude modules. Edition 2018 re-exports v1 only, while 2021+ add TryFrom/TryInto/FromIterator, and 2024+ additionally add Future/IntoFuture.\n- library/std/src/prelude/mod.rs (lines 114-177): Mirror structure with corresponding edition-specific modules re-exporting appropriate items from core and std.\n- library/core/src/prelude/v1.rs and library/std/src/prelude/v1.rs: Define the base v1 prelude items that all editions share.\n\nBoth library/std/src/lib.rs and library/core/src/lib.rs use the #[prelude_import] attribute (lines 426-428 and 218-220 respectively) to automatically inject the edition-appropriate prelude via the compiler.\n\n**Edition-Based Macro_use and Prelude Injection (compiler/):**\n\nThe compiler/rustc_builtin_macros/src/standard_library_imports.rs::inject function handles edition-specific prelude injection:\n- Line 42: Uses edition >= Edition2018 to determine ident_span behavior (2015 uses call_site, 2018+ uses span)\n- Lines 50-61: Selects the appropriate prelude module path based on edition: rust_2015, rust_2018, rust_2021, rust_2024, or rust_future\n- Line 46: Injects a #[macro_use] attribute on the auto-generated extern crate for std/core\n\n**Resolver Behavior Differences:**\n\nThe resolver in compiler/rustc_resolve/ implements critical edition differences:\n\n1. Path Resolution (compiler/rustc_resolve/src/lib.rs, lines 436-449): Defines three ModuleOrUniformRoot variants for edition differences:\n   - ModuleAndExternPrelude: Used for paths (::) from 2015 edition macros used in 2018+ crates\n   - ExternPrelude: Used for paths (::) on 2018 edition only\n   - These allow 2015 macros to resolve paths through both the crate root and extern prelude, while 2018+ resolves only through extern prelude\n\n2. Import Graph Building (compiler/rustc_resolve/src/build_reduced_graph.rs):\n   - Lines 545-560: Edition-specific crate root prepending. In 2015 edition, imports without explicit crate root get '::' prepended if they're in 2015 context.\n   - Lines 670-684: Special handling for prelude imports marked with #[prelude_import], resolved early and stored as the crate's prelude\n   - Lines 936-980: Extern crate handling with macro_use processing\n   - Lines 1074-1100: Macro use imports processing for both specific and wildcard macros\n\n3. Identifier Resolution (compiler/rustc_resolve/src/ident.rs, lines 1785-1810):\n   - Line 1787-1789: For 2018+ code, '::' paths resolve to ExternPrelude\n   - Lines 1791-1798: For 2015 macros used in 2018+ crates, '::' paths resolve to ModuleAndExternPrelude (allowing fallback to module root)\n   - This enables the \"mixed edition\" scenario where 2015 macros maintain their old path semantics\n\n4. Diagnostic Path Resolution (compiler/rustc_resolve/src/late/diagnostics.rs, lines 304-316):\n   - Line 304: Checks if edition > Edition2015\n   - 2018+: '::foo' syntax only pulls from extern prelude (no crate root fallback)\n   - 2015: '::foo' resolves from crate root\n\n**Scope Sets and Prelude Handling:**\n\ncompiler/rustc_resolve/src/lib.rs defines Scope enum (lines 130-143) with StdLibPrelude variant (line 140) for items introduced by the internal #[prelude_import] import, separate from MacroUsePrelude and other scopes. The ScopeSet enum (lines 148-157) includes ModuleAndExternPrelude for handling mixed 2015-2018 mode in macros."
}

